### Trigger workflow
POST http://localhost:7071/api/workflow/trigger HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pg_host_prod": "advpsqlfxuk",
  "pg_host_dev": "advpsqlfxukdev",
  "pg_database": "test01",
  "pg_user": "alfonsod",
  "resource_group": "adv_data_rg"
}

### Check workflow status (all runs)
GET http://localhost:7071/api/workflow/status HTTP/1.1

### Check workflow status (specific run)
GET http://localhost:7071/api/workflow/status?run_id=12345678 HTTP/1.1

### Health check
GET http://localhost:7071/api/health HTTP/1.1

### Test endpoint
GET http://localhost:7071/api/test HTTP/1.1

### Ver configuración actual
GET http://localhost:7071/api/config HTTP/1.1

### cURL examples

# Trigger workflow
curl -X POST http://localhost:7071/api/workflow/trigger \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "pg_host_prod": "advpsqlfxuk",
    "pg_host_dev": "advpsqlfxukdev",
    "pg_database": "test01",
    "pg_user": "alfonsod",
    "resource_group": "adv_data_rg"
  }'

# Check status of all workflows
curl http://localhost:7071/api/workflow/status

# Check status of a specific workflow run
curl http://localhost:7071/api/workflow/status?run_id=12345678

# Health check
curl http://localhost:7071/api/health

# Test endpoint
curl http://localhost:7071/api/test

# Ver configuración
curl http://localhost:7071/api/config